39:11.320 --> 39:13.300
We can seek a restraining order,

39:13.400 --> 39:15.500
which will prohibit him
from coming near you.

39:15.600 --> 39:19.060
But, I should warn you
that sometimes antagonizes them.

39:19.160 --> 39:20.620
Escalates the behavior.

39:20.720 --> 39:21.860
Great.

39:21.960 --> 39:24.020
I typically advise people
in your situation

39:24.120 --> 39:26.500
to keep a record
of every incident of harassment.

39:26.600 --> 39:30.420
If he calls you, texts you, follows you,
write it down.

39:30.520 --> 39:32.249
This will help give
your claim credibility.

39:32.720 --> 39:34.290
Call me anytime.

39:34.920 --> 39:37.100
And, of course, if you ever feel
in any physical danger,

39:37.200 --> 39:38.860
call 911 immediately.

39:38.960 --> 39:42.965
If we catch him in the act,
it makes our job a whole lot easier.

39:46.560 --> 39:47.891
Thank you.

40:39.520 --> 40:41.045
(RATTLING)

40:59.680 --> 41:01.205
(GASPING)

41:09.000 --> 41:10.161
(CAR ALARM CHIRPS)

41:16.320 --> 41:17.560
(ENGINE TURNS OVER)

41:22.800 --> 41:26.180
And I'll manage the remote server
until you're fully up to speed.

41:26.280 --> 41:27.420
- Great.
- That way we can...

41:27.520 --> 41:29.500
- (PHONE BEEPS)
- RECEPTIONIST: Mr. Forsythe,

41:29.600 --> 41:31.020
can you come out here for a moment?

41:31.120 --> 41:32.451
Excuse me, hmm?

41:35.120 --> 41:36.100
- Yes, sir.
- SHERIFF: Yes, I'm here

41:36.200 --> 41:37.565
to see Mr. Carter Duncan.

41:37.680 --> 41:38.806
I understand he's in this office.

41:39.400 --> 41:41.180
MR. FORSYTHE: Uh, in regard to?

41:41.280 --> 41:43.601
SHERIFF:
I have something to deliver to him.

41:47.560 --> 41:49.050
Carter Duncan?

41:50.400 --> 41:52.580
- Yes.
- You're hereby served.

41:52.680 --> 41:56.380
This is a temporary restraining order
issued by the LA County Sheriff's office.

41:56.480 --> 41:59.620
You are legally prohibited
from contacting Miss Leah Vaughn.

41:59.720 --> 42:02.820
You're further ordered to maintain
a distance of no less than 50 yards

42:02.920 --> 42:05.780
from Miss Vaughn's person,
her residence and workplace.

42:05.880 --> 42:08.121
You have any questions, Mr. Duncan?

42:09.000 --> 42:10.331
Have a good day.

42:12.280 --> 42:13.540
- Mr. Forsythe...
- Carter!

42:13.640 --> 42:14.971
You better go.

42:16.120 --> 42:17.201
Now!

43:10.640 --> 43:11.687
(CAT MEOWING)

43:42.960 --> 43:44.644
(DOORKNOB RATTLES)

44:13.520 --> 44:14.726
(DOOR CLOSES)

44:16.960 --> 44:18.450
(CAR STARTING)

44:20.560 --> 44:22.130
(CAR LEAVING)

44:35.600 --> 44:36.965
(SNIFFING)

44:55.680 --> 44:57.444
(KEYBOARD CLACKING)

45:30.840 --> 45:31.841
Rusty.

45:37.640 --> 45:39.005
Rusty.

45:49.440 --> 45:50.680
Rusty.

45:56.360 --> 45:57.566
Rusty?

45:57.840 --> 45:59.001
Rusty!

45:59.840 --> 46:01.740
Has Rusty gone missing again?

46:01.840 --> 46:03.100
Yeah.

46:03.200 --> 46:05.646
- You haven't seen him?
- No. Sorry.

46:06.080 --> 46:08.300
- (SIGHS)
- I'll keep an eye out.

46:08.400 --> 46:10.004
Okay. Good night.

46:12.520 --> 46:13.760
Rusty!

46:19.680 --> 46:21.409
(KEYBOARD CLACKING)

46:29.280 --> 46:30.645
(LINE RINGING)

46:34.560 --> 46:35.780
VOICEMAIL:
Hi, you've reached Leah Vaughn.

46:35.880 --> 46:37.740
I'm not in right now.
Leave a message and I'll...

46:37.840 --> 46:39.729
- (PHONE BEEPS)
- (CAT MEWLING)

46:44.720 --> 46:47.220
I haven't heard from him
since I changed my number the last time.

46:47.320 --> 46:48.500
KAREN: Maybe you're in the clear.

46:48.600 --> 46:50.220
Yeah, maybe three times is a charm.

46:50.320 --> 46:51.460
- Well, be careful.
- Okay.

46:51.560 --> 46:52.540
Call me tomorrow.

46:52.640 --> 46:53.971
- Bye.
- Bye.

46:59.040 --> 47:00.121
(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

47:01.240 --> 47:03.208
LEAH: God damn it!

47:04.400 --> 47:06.528
- Listen, you asshole!
- DAVE: Leah?

47:07.360 --> 47:08.964
Hey, it's me.

47:11.040 --> 47:12.020
Dave?

47:12.120 --> 47:13.420
Karen gave me your new number

47:13.520 --> 47:18.162
and she told me
that you were, um, seeing someone.

47:18.720 --> 47:20.529
Oh, I'm not anymore.

47:22.520 --> 47:23.601
Really?

47:23.880 --> 47:25.723
Listen, you think I can see you?

47:25.920 --> 47:28.241
So we can just talk in person?

47:30.320 --> 47:32.084
I'd love to see you.

47:34.080 --> 47:35.650
I've missed you.

47:38.640 --> 47:43.168
I want you to know
that I've been thinking about you.

47:43.640 --> 47:45.290
A lot, actually.

47:45.560 --> 47:46.607
Yeah, me too.

47:47.120 --> 47:50.500
I also want you to know
that I meant what I said that night.

47:50.600 --> 47:51.780
What's that?

47:51.880 --> 47:54.121
That I never want to lose you.

47:56.320 --> 47:57.446
I love you.

48:00.160 --> 48:02.060
I thought a lot
about what you said that night,

48:02.160 --> 48:04.162
and it's a huge decision.

48:04.480 --> 48:06.323
Not to be rushed into.

48:07.800 --> 48:12.124
I think I jump into things sometimes.

48:16.200 --> 48:18.202
So, how about we do this?

48:19.520 --> 48:22.569
How about we start over?

48:25.960 --> 48:27.086
(CHUCKLES)

48:35.360 --> 48:36.521
(MEWLING)

48:48.360 --> 48:49.850
(CAR STARTING)

48:57.400 --> 48:58.731
LEAH: Thank you.

49:04.520 --> 49:05.646
Thank you.

49:06.120 --> 49:07.531
- Thanks.
- Enjoy.

49:09.040 --> 49:10.246
So, is this okay?

49:10.600 --> 49:12.100
You know I love it here.

49:12.200 --> 49:13.201
(CHUCKLES)

49:21.040 --> 49:22.121
Shit.

49:23.960 --> 49:25.086
What?

49:25.320 --> 49:26.606
I can't believe he's here.

49:28.560 --> 49:30.100
- Who?
- LEAH: I'm sorry.

49:30.200 --> 49:31.201
Um...

49:33.440 --> 49:35.442
- Can we leave?
- Leave?

49:36.080 --> 49:37.570
Now, please?

49:38.640 --> 49:40.620
I don't understand.
Who are you looking at?

49:40.720 --> 49:43.200
That guy I told you about. Carter.

49:44.000 --> 49:46.082
He just sat down at the bar.

49:47.200 --> 49:49.089
No, don't. Don't look.

49:51.040 --> 49:52.201
Jesus!

49:52.920 --> 49:53.921
He, uh...

49:56.280 --> 49:58.521
He probably followed us here.

49:59.360 --> 50:00.900
- Let's go, okay?
- No, no, no.

50:01.000 --> 50:02.764
We're not gonna go.

50:03.400 --> 50:05.460
Listen, let me handle this. Okay?

50:05.560 --> 50:07.050
No. No.

50:07.520 --> 50:08.500
Please don't, Dave.

50:08.600 --> 50:12.420
I don't want you to antagonize him.
He's crazy!

50:12.520 --> 50:14.488
I'm just gonna go over there
and talk to him, man to man.

50:15.040 --> 50:16.565
All right? That's it.

50:16.920 --> 50:18.365
It'll be that simple.

50:27.040 --> 50:28.405
Carter, right?

50:30.240 --> 50:31.730
Do I know you?

50:32.240 --> 50:36.290
DAVE: Just want you to know that you're
upsetting the young lady over there.

50:36.400 --> 50:39.006
And your presence here isn't welcome.

50:39.280 --> 50:41.282
It's a public place, man.

50:44.680 --> 50:46.682
What are you doing, man?

50:47.000 --> 50:48.001
Huh?

50:49.760 --> 50:52.900
She doesn't want anything
to do with you, okay?

50:53.000 --> 50:55.321
So, maybe it's time you take the hint

50:55.720 --> 50:57.245
and move along.

50:58.640 --> 50:59.971
Dave, is it?

51:03.280 --> 51:05.089
I know all about you.

51:06.840 --> 51:10.049
How much of a pussy you were
for not stepping up.

51:14.600 --> 51:16.820
You think you got a second shot.

51:16.920 --> 51:19.048
I get it. You're threatened.

51:19.320 --> 51:22.130
- Maybe I'm still in the picture.
- (CHUCKLES)

51:23.920 --> 51:25.365
Let me tell you something, man.

51:26.720 --> 51:29.929
You are so far out of the picture

51:31.080 --> 51:32.525
it's not even funny.

51:37.920 --> 51:39.046
Am I?

51:42.640 --> 51:43.687
Am I?

51:48.880 --> 51:50.325
Look at her.

51:52.040 --> 51:53.121
Yeah.

51:53.720 --> 51:56.041
Probably remembering the sex right now.

51:56.560 --> 51:57.580
(CROWD GASP)

51:57.680 --> 51:59.205
- Hey! Whoa, whoa, whoa.
- Shut up!

52:04.040 --> 52:06.008
You mess with her again,

52:06.640 --> 52:08.608
you even look at her again,

52:11.680 --> 52:14.604
I'm gonna wipe that smug
look off your face.

52:15.360 --> 52:16.725
Permanently.

52:26.480 --> 52:27.561
Try me, okay?

52:30.000 --> 52:31.729
I want you to try me.

52:44.400 --> 52:46.220
LEAH:
What happened? What did you say to him?

52:46.320 --> 52:49.220
I just told him
that if he bothers you again,

52:49.320 --> 52:51.260
I was gonna rip his head off.

52:51.360 --> 52:53.681
- LEAH: You said that?
- DAVE: Yes, I said that.

52:54.280 --> 52:56.601
I'm not gonna let him mess with you.

52:57.000 --> 52:58.001
Okay?

53:01.160 --> 53:03.242
See? Apparently it worked.

53:03.880 --> 53:06.724
I don't think you have to worry about him
bothering you again.

53:08.440 --> 53:11.523
DAVE: You sure you're gonna
be okay here tonight? Alone?

53:12.320 --> 53:13.367
Yeah.

53:14.120 --> 53:15.281
Okay.

53:16.440 --> 53:19.649
Okay. Well, if you ever need
anything, just,

53:20.800 --> 53:22.609
just give me a call.

53:26.240 --> 53:27.321
(LEAH CHUCKLES)

53:29.600 --> 53:30.681
Leah.

53:32.320 --> 53:33.580
Am I wasting my time?

53:33.680 --> 53:35.011
No!

53:35.960 --> 53:37.200
No.

53:45.560 --> 53:46.925
Good night.

53:47.320 --> 53:48.651
Good night.

53:55.520 --> 53:56.851
(CAR STARTING)

54:05.120 --> 54:06.565
DETECTIVE HANSEN:
You know why you're here?

54:08.640 --> 54:10.483
Two weeks ago,
you were served a court order

54:10.600 --> 54:13.206
to avoid all contact with Leah Vaughn.

54:13.960 --> 54:15.086
Oh, yeah.

54:19.440 --> 54:22.700
You seem pretty relaxed
for a guy with a court order against him.

54:22.800 --> 54:24.290
CARTER:
It's just a piece of paper, Detective.

54:26.440 --> 54:30.923
Yeah, well, that piece of paper says
you're not to come within 50 yards of her.

54:32.480 --> 54:33.891
So?

54:34.360 --> 54:37.762
So, you violated that order
by being in that restaurant last night.

54:42.720 --> 54:45.060
It's a public place, Detective.

54:45.160 --> 54:47.049
I had no idea she was there.

54:47.680 --> 54:51.820
When I was alerted to her presence,
I immediately left the premises.

54:51.920 --> 54:55.003
I've got witnesses to prove it,
including Miss Vaughn herself.

54:56.040 --> 54:58.361
In fact, if anyone should be complaining

54:58.480 --> 55:00.580
about the way in which
they were treated last night,

55:00.680 --> 55:02.444
it's me.

55:04.200 --> 55:05.281
How's that?

55:06.320 --> 55:08.940
Well, when her dinner companion
came to me,

55:09.040 --> 55:12.965
he grabbed me by the throat
and threatened me.

55:15.200 --> 55:18.010
I'm no detective,
but it seems to me that

55:18.640 --> 55:21.405
that's grounds for filing
a restraining order against him.

55:24.600 --> 55:26.011
What do you think?

55:27.080 --> 55:28.241
Let me tell you what I think.

55:33.840 --> 55:36.684
I think you better be careful,
Mr. Duncan.

55:37.120 --> 55:38.980
Because some shit's gonna come
down on you,

55:39.080 --> 55:43.244
and it's gonna come down hard,
if you don't leave that woman alone.

55:45.240 --> 55:46.571
You got it?

55:50.880 --> 55:52.405
I got it.

55:55.840 --> 55:58.286
I'll be watching you, Mr. Duncan.

56:05.040 --> 56:06.929
Am I free to go now?

56:09.080 --> 56:10.161
Be my guest.

56:20.840 --> 56:22.980
He's full of shit. Pull his rap sheet.

56:23.080 --> 56:24.491
You got it.

56:53.520 --> 56:55.100
MRS. McCARTHY: What are you doing?

56:55.200 --> 56:57.885
Mrs. McCarthy! You startled me.

56:58.480 --> 56:59.820
What are you doing?

56:59.920 --> 57:02.060
Leah wanted me to wait for her here.

57:02.160 --> 57:04.322
She told me you guys broke up.

57:07.680 --> 57:09.045
We're back together now.

57:14.720 --> 57:17.564
When was the last time
you talked to her about it?

57:19.080 --> 57:20.100
Um...

57:20.200 --> 57:23.761
Never mind. You know,
I was keeping an eye out for her.

57:34.600 --> 57:35.601
(GASPS)

57:39.240 --> 57:40.321
(WHIMPERING)

57:55.240 --> 57:56.540
(DOORKNOB RATTLING)

57:56.640 --> 57:58.210
(POUNDING ON DOOR)

57:58.720 --> 57:59.881
(GASPING)

58:03.360 --> 58:04.725
(DOORKNOB RATTLING)

58:07.800 --> 58:09.211
(POUNDING CONTINUES)

58:15.760 --> 58:17.171
(DOORKNOB RATTLING)

58:21.560 --> 58:23.642
- (RATTLING STOPS)
- (PANTING)

58:30.600 --> 58:32.204
(MUFFLED SCREAM)

58:40.440 --> 58:41.805
(SCREAMING)

58:59.280 --> 59:01.940
He's never been gone this long.
I hope a coyote didn't get him.

59:02.040 --> 59:03.580
No. A coyote didn't get him.

59:03.680 --> 59:05.125
He'll be fine.

59:13.640 --> 59:14.820
I'm gonna hop in the shower.

59:14.920 --> 59:17.241
- Would you unzip me?
- Of course.

59:20.640 --> 59:23.405
- You want to open a bottle of wine?
- Mmm.

59:24.160 --> 59:26.322
- I won't be long.
- All right.

01:00:19.800 --> 01:00:20.940
(LEAH GASPS)

01:00:21.040 --> 01:00:22.565
- (BOTH CHUCKLE)
- LEAH: Oh, my God.

01:00:27.880 --> 01:00:30.281
(LEAH MOANING SOFTLY)

01:01:05.480 --> 01:01:06.925
There you go.

01:01:08.640 --> 01:01:10.529
I need to get my phone.

01:01:11.240 --> 01:01:12.890
- Be right back.
- Okay.

01:02:15.120 --> 01:02:16.610
(LEAH MOANING)

01:02:56.680 --> 01:02:57.727
LEAH: Happy birthday, honey.

01:02:59.320 --> 01:03:00.940
It was my birthday three months ago.

01:03:01.040 --> 01:03:05.762
I know, but I bought you a present
before we broke up.

01:03:06.560 --> 01:03:08.210
And you kept it?

01:03:08.680 --> 01:03:11.251
Believe me, I would've taken it back,

01:03:11.720 --> 01:03:14.803
but I got it engraved.

01:03:22.720 --> 01:03:23.721
Wow.

01:03:35.880 --> 01:03:37.291
You like it?

01:03:38.560 --> 01:03:40.260
- I love it.
- (CHUCKLES)

01:03:40.360 --> 01:03:41.691
I love it.

01:03:52.400 --> 01:03:54.209
Let me put it on you.

01:04:04.760 --> 01:04:06.649
It is beautiful, babe.

01:04:07.600 --> 01:04:09.250
It's beautiful.

01:04:09.840 --> 01:04:12.081
I'm never gonna take this off.

01:04:12.600 --> 01:04:13.840
- Ever?
- Ever.

01:04:15.360 --> 01:04:16.600
- Ever!
- (BOTH CHUCKLE)

01:04:19.880 --> 01:04:21.689
You are incredible, you know that?

01:04:25.000 --> 01:04:26.126
In...

01:04:29.600 --> 01:04:31.170
- Cred...
- (CHUCKLES)

01:05:07.640 --> 01:05:09.580
- He's just playing with me.
- I get it.

01:05:09.680 --> 01:05:11.740
He's out there. He's watching me!

01:05:11.840 --> 01:05:12.860
He's got my cat.

01:05:12.960 --> 01:05:15.100
I'm gonna try to get a subpoena
to search his apartment.

01:05:15.200 --> 01:05:16.580
How long will that take?

01:05:16.680 --> 01:05:18.220
Hopefully, only a few days.

01:05:18.320 --> 01:05:20.500
In the meantime, I'm digging more,

01:05:20.600 --> 01:05:22.409
and I'm gonna bring him back in
for questioning.

01:05:22.520 --> 01:05:23.660
We did find out this.

01:05:23.760 --> 01:05:26.460
Carter Duncan is not Carter Duncan.

01:05:26.560 --> 01:05:28.540
He changed his name in 2003.

01:05:28.640 --> 01:05:29.940
All legal,

01:05:30.040 --> 01:05:33.522
but maybe there's more here
than just a jealous ex-boyfriend.

01:05:47.640 --> 01:05:49.260
- What's going on?
- Who are you?

01:05:49.360 --> 01:05:51.647
I'm Leah Vaughn, her neighbor.
Is she all right?

01:05:51.760 --> 01:05:53.888
Looks like she took a fall
down the basement stairs.

01:05:54.520 --> 01:05:56.980
- Oh, my God.
- I'm afraid she's dead, ma'am.

01:05:57.080 --> 01:05:58.366
- What?
- She broke her neck.

01:05:59.800 --> 01:06:00.860
Oh, my God!

01:06:00.960 --> 01:06:02.325
When was the last time you saw her?

01:06:05.080 --> 01:06:06.980
- Ma'am?
- I, I, I don't,

01:06:07.080 --> 01:06:08.525
I don't remember.

01:06:09.040 --> 01:06:10.300
When did this happen?

01:06:10.400 --> 01:06:12.721
Forensics thinks it happened
some time ago. At least a week.

01:06:13.200 --> 01:06:15.180
Her daughter, who lives out of town,
finally called it in

01:06:15.280 --> 01:06:16.620
when she didn't return any of her calls.

01:06:16.720 --> 01:06:17.940
DISPATCHER: Charlie-22, come in.

01:06:18.040 --> 01:06:19.140
Ma'am.

01:06:19.240 --> 01:06:20.446
Oh, my God.

01:06:29.240 --> 01:06:30.924
- Morning.
- Morning.

01:06:39.760 --> 01:06:41.603
- (PHONE BEEPS)
- RACHEL: Leah.

01:06:42.080 --> 01:06:44.651
LEAH:
Just take a message, please, Rachel.

01:06:44.800 --> 01:06:47.804
Mr. Renkin wants to see you
in the boardroom.

01:06:47.920 --> 01:06:49.001
Now.

01:07:01.520 --> 01:07:03.010
(LEAH MOANING)

01:07:04.760 --> 01:07:05.886
This is bullshit.

01:07:06.000 --> 01:07:08.321
That email went out this morning
from your account.

01:07:08.960 --> 01:07:10.610
My account? What?

01:07:10.720 --> 01:07:13.007
All of our clients have been calling.
They're beyond outraged.

01:07:13.200 --> 01:07:16.020
I don't have to tell you what this'll do
to the Prop 37 campaign.

01:07:16.120 --> 01:07:17.540
Or to the reputation of this firm.

01:07:17.640 --> 01:07:19.980
And I don't know of any
serious advocacy group

01:07:20.080 --> 01:07:22.420
that won't think twice
about asking us to represent them.

01:07:22.520 --> 01:07:25.046
Tom, I... I can fix this.

01:07:26.720 --> 01:07:27.860
I can fix it.

01:07:27.960 --> 01:07:29.849
TOM: I don't think you can.

01:07:31.080 --> 01:07:32.241
We're going to have to suspend you.

01:07:32.360 --> 01:07:36.700
You know me, Tom. I would never
jeopardize my work, my reputation,

01:07:36.800 --> 01:07:38.643
or the reputation of this company.

01:07:39.560 --> 01:07:41.050
Yeah, I know, Leah.

01:07:41.160 --> 01:07:43.700
Just have to see how this plays out

01:07:43.800 --> 01:07:45.928
but my hands are tied, here.

01:07:46.040 --> 01:07:47.540
Can't you see I've been set up?

01:07:47.640 --> 01:07:51.486
That email went to Senator Wharton, too.
You know that, right?

01:07:57.400 --> 01:07:59.220
LEAH: I know he did this.

01:07:59.320 --> 01:08:00.340
I know he did.

01:08:00.440 --> 01:08:02.660
- You need to tell the detective about this.
- LEAH: I did.

01:08:02.760 --> 01:08:05.684
I told him, and he said
he would look into it.

01:08:05.920 --> 01:08:07.445
- Have you talked to Dave?
- No.

01:08:07.560 --> 01:08:11.060
He's in Malibu with a client.
I didn't want to distract him.

01:08:11.160 --> 01:08:13.128
I'll tell him later tonight
when he gets home.

01:08:15.240 --> 01:08:17.004
(DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE)

01:08:22.680 --> 01:08:24.011
MAN: Thanks again for making the drive.

01:08:24.120 --> 01:08:25.460
DAVE: No problem.
I'll get these changes to you soon.

01:08:25.560 --> 01:08:26.890
- MAN: Thank you.
- DAVE: Talk to you soon.

01:08:33.000 --> 01:08:35.140
(CELL PHONE DIALING)

01:08:35.240 --> 01:08:36.479
(LINE RINGING)

01:08:37.279 --> 01:08:39.260
VOICEMAIL: Hi, you've reached
Leah Vaughn. I'm not in right now.

01:08:39.359 --> 01:08:41.899
Leave a message and I'll call you back.

01:08:42.000 --> 01:08:44.060
Hey, I'm just calling to let to know
that I'm on my way.

01:08:44.160 --> 01:08:46.447
I should be there around 11:00.

01:08:46.600 --> 01:08:49.206
I cannot wait to see you. I love you.

01:08:58.200 --> 01:08:59.439
(TIRES SQUEAL)

01:09:18.160 --> 01:09:19.207
(TIRE RATTLING)

01:09:20.319 --> 01:09:21.651
What the hell is that?

01:09:25.800 --> 01:09:26.961
(TIRES SQUEALING)

01:10:10.440 --> 01:10:12.090
(GROANING)

01:10:16.480 --> 01:10:18.209
(COUGHING)

01:10:34.120 --> 01:10:35.281
Shh.

01:10:38.960 --> 01:10:40.928
(MUFFLED GRUNTING)

01:10:49.480 --> 01:10:50.686
(GRUNTING STOPS)

01:11:15.520 --> 01:11:18.020
LEAH: Hey. Uh, I'm a little worried.

01:11:18.120 --> 01:11:22.603
It's after midnight,
and, uh, you're not home yet.

01:11:23.560 --> 01:11:26.006
I'm waiting up, so call me, okay?

01:11:27.280 --> 01:11:28.884
I love you, too.

01:11:41.160 --> 01:11:42.446
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

01:11:43.560 --> 01:11:45.369
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

01:11:59.800 --> 01:12:00.980
What are you doing here?

01:12:01.080 --> 01:12:02.860
- We need to talk.
- What?

01:12:02.960 --> 01:12:05.327
- May I come in?
- What happened?

01:12:06.560 --> 01:12:07.925
It's Dave.

01:12:08.720 --> 01:12:10.722
He was in a car accident.

01:12:11.920 --> 01:12:13.888
Oh, my God! (STAMMERS) Is he okay?

01:12:14.600 --> 01:12:15.700
Leah, I'm sorry.

01:12:15.800 --> 01:12:17.300
He didn't survive.

01:12:17.400 --> 01:12:18.740
Oh, my God. No!

01:12:18.840 --> 01:12:19.820
I'm so sorry.

01:12:19.920 --> 01:12:21.180
No, no, no, please.

01:12:21.280 --> 01:12:22.700
(VOICE BREAKING) No, please.

01:12:22.800 --> 01:12:24.245
(SOBBING) No, no, no.

01:12:26.520 --> 01:12:28.727
Please, God!

01:12:54.480 --> 01:12:55.481
(SIGHS)

01:13:08.680 --> 01:13:09.681
(GASPS)

01:13:10.120 --> 01:13:11.540
According to the report,

01:13:11.640 --> 01:13:14.180
Dave wasn't wearing a watch
at the scene of the accident.

01:13:14.280 --> 01:13:15.540
But he was.

01:13:15.640 --> 01:13:17.642
I'd just given it to him.

01:13:18.320 --> 01:13:20.243
He promised me he'd never take it off.

01:13:24.640 --> 01:13:25.766
Don't you see?

01:13:25.880 --> 01:13:29.060
Carter was there.
He took the watch and now he's...

01:13:29.160 --> 01:13:33.540
I want you to know,
how we proceed from this point further

01:13:33.640 --> 01:13:36.211
is critical if we want to catch him.

01:13:37.440 --> 01:13:38.980
What was his real name again?

01:13:39.080 --> 01:13:40.340
Robert Adams.

01:13:40.440 --> 01:13:43.980
He's not who he says he is.
He's been lying about everything.

01:13:44.080 --> 01:13:45.620
Why can't you just arrest him?

01:13:45.720 --> 01:13:47.740
He changed his name legally.

01:13:47.840 --> 01:13:49.900
And yes, he's been arrested before
for harassment,

01:13:50.000 --> 01:13:51.060
but nothing ever stuck.

01:13:51.160 --> 01:13:52.810
That's bullshit!

01:13:53.680 --> 01:13:55.260
You showed me his record.

01:13:55.360 --> 01:13:57.620
He's been in and out of trouble
his whole life.

01:13:57.720 --> 01:13:58.740
You said it yourself.

01:13:58.840 --> 01:14:02.620
(STUTTERING) He's, what, bipolar?
What was it?

01:14:02.720 --> 01:14:05.100
Bipolar, devolving into psychosis.

01:14:05.200 --> 01:14:07.140
What they used to call
psychopathic behavior.

01:14:07.240 --> 01:14:08.940
But just because he was diagnosed
doesn't mean that...

01:14:09.040 --> 01:14:11.220
He killed Dave and this is your proof!

01:14:11.320 --> 01:14:12.820
I can't just keep hauling him in.

01:14:12.920 --> 01:14:14.649
I need evidence or we'll never get him.

01:14:17.880 --> 01:14:19.962
I want him just as bad
as you do, believe me.

01:14:20.800 --> 01:14:23.780
We found no surveillance equipment,
and there's still no sign of him, sir.

01:14:23.880 --> 01:14:26.201
Also, no signs of forced entry anywhere.

01:14:29.960 --> 01:14:31.780
Did you give him a key?

01:14:31.880 --> 01:14:33.006
Shit!

01:14:34.040 --> 01:14:35.121
What?

01:14:35.960 --> 01:14:40.010
He was with me one night
when I locked myself out of the house.

01:14:42.240 --> 01:14:46.290
He saw where I hid my spare key.
He's obviously been here.

01:14:46.560 --> 01:14:48.580
You can arrest him
for breaking and entering.

01:14:48.680 --> 01:14:50.284
Not unless we can prove it.

01:14:51.320 --> 01:14:54.300
I'll have Forensics
look at the watch and the key.

01:14:54.400 --> 01:14:56.860
If Carter left a print,

01:14:56.960 --> 01:14:59.660
or if there's even a microscopic trace
of Dave's blood on it,

01:14:59.760 --> 01:15:01.740
then we've got him
on breaking and entering.

01:15:01.840 --> 01:15:03.251
Possibly murder.

01:15:09.000 --> 01:15:10.286
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

01:15:10.400 --> 01:15:11.640
(SIGHS)

01:15:17.120 --> 01:15:18.610
DETECTIVE HANSEN: He's a robot.

01:15:23.440 --> 01:15:25.660
Turn that thing off.

01:15:25.760 --> 01:15:27.285
What are you gonna do?

01:15:46.920 --> 01:15:49.207
I want you to tell me
what happened to David King.

01:15:51.160 --> 01:15:53.100
CARTER: I don't know David King.

01:15:53.200 --> 01:15:55.089
(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

01:15:55.320 --> 01:15:57.561
Maybe I should talk to Robert.

01:15:58.120 --> 01:16:00.740
You see, I know who you are, Robert.

01:16:00.840 --> 01:16:01.860
(VIBRATING CONTINUES)

01:16:01.960 --> 01:16:03.724
CARTER: No. You don't know.

01:16:06.320 --> 01:16:07.560
Don't I?

01:16:10.360 --> 01:16:11.646
(GASPS)

01:16:15.280 --> 01:16:17.647
DETECTIVE HANSEN: I know you changed
your name 10 years ago.

01:16:18.960 --> 01:16:22.043
I know you were abandoned
by your mother at age two.

01:16:22.480 --> 01:16:25.643
I know you grew up in foster homes
in Illinois.

01:16:25.800 --> 01:16:28.940
You were in and out of trouble
until the age of 17.

01:16:29.040 --> 01:16:32.522
And I know you have a very high IQ.

01:16:33.160 --> 01:16:35.180
But, Robert,

01:16:35.280 --> 01:16:37.681
you're not as smart
as you think you are.

01:16:39.160 --> 01:16:40.889
You hacked into her computer.

01:16:42.520 --> 01:16:44.420
You broke into her house.

01:16:44.520 --> 01:16:46.010
You got proof?

01:16:51.320 --> 01:16:52.446
This look familiar?

01:16:59.320 --> 01:17:01.340
What if I were to tell you
we had your prints on this watch,

01:17:01.440 --> 01:17:03.568
and we know you moved it
from the crime scene?

01:17:05.440 --> 01:17:06.851
I'd say

01:17:08.040 --> 01:17:09.405
try harder.

01:17:20.760 --> 01:17:23.650
It must have killed you
to see her with him.

01:17:26.280 --> 01:17:27.691
Every day,

01:17:28.560 --> 01:17:29.925
every night.

01:17:31.520 --> 01:17:34.251
Knowing someone else was kissing her,

01:17:37.000 --> 01:17:38.525
touching her,

01:17:40.560 --> 01:17:41.971
having her.

01:17:45.560 --> 01:17:47.449
And you were watching.

01:17:48.080 --> 01:17:49.445
Weren't you?

01:17:49.640 --> 01:17:51.608
You just couldn't stop.

01:17:53.400 --> 01:17:54.765
Could you?

01:17:55.760 --> 01:17:57.649
Are we finished, here?

01:18:01.280 --> 01:18:04.329
Or do you want to talk about
something else?

01:18:25.800 --> 01:18:27.131
(CARTER GRUNTS)

01:18:30.040 --> 01:18:32.566
Did you hit your head, Robert?

01:18:32.920 --> 01:18:33.967
(CARTER COUGHS)

01:18:35.760 --> 01:18:37.967
I told you to be more careful.

01:18:47.640 --> 01:18:49.449
The email is untraceable.

01:18:50.400 --> 01:18:53.380
- It came from your computer.
- (SCOFFS) Of course it did.

01:18:53.480 --> 01:18:55.100
But you're right.

01:18:55.200 --> 01:18:56.247
The suicide note?

01:18:56.360 --> 01:18:57.850
It's a threat.

01:18:58.640 --> 01:18:59.700
And the watch?

01:18:59.800 --> 01:19:01.006
Clean.

01:19:06.880 --> 01:19:08.689
So, you can't protect me?

01:19:10.840 --> 01:19:12.888
I'm doing everything
I can within the law.

01:19:14.640 --> 01:19:17.166
I think you should go away
for a little while.

01:19:17.640 --> 01:19:19.220
I'm not gonna let him run me off.

01:19:19.320 --> 01:19:20.380
Maybe your parents?

01:19:20.480 --> 01:19:24.451
And I'm not gonna put my parents at risk
with that sick bastard.

01:19:24.720 --> 01:19:25.740
Okay.

01:19:25.840 --> 01:19:28.491
He destroyed everything I care about.

01:19:31.440 --> 01:19:33.841
And I'm not just gonna roll over.

01:19:34.600 --> 01:19:35.840
I'm not.

01:19:38.360 --> 01:19:39.460
(SIGHS)

01:19:39.560 --> 01:19:41.210
I can see that.

01:19:42.560 --> 01:19:43.971
What would you do?

01:19:48.720 --> 01:19:50.370
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

01:19:57.040 --> 01:19:58.724
It's time for my coffee break.

01:19:59.320 --> 01:20:00.500
You're welcome to join me.

01:20:00.600 --> 01:20:01.940
Excuse me?

01:20:02.040 --> 01:20:04.168
It's just across the street.

01:20:04.960 --> 01:20:06.200
(SCOFFS)

01:20:16.920 --> 01:20:19.446
What kind of game
are you playing with me?

01:20:20.480 --> 01:20:22.700
You asked me what I would do.

01:20:22.800 --> 01:20:26.964
I can't give a victim that kind
of advice as a member of the force.

01:20:27.240 --> 01:20:29.460
But there's nothing preventing me
from telling a friend

01:20:29.560 --> 01:20:31.801
a story over a cup of coffee.

01:20:36.320 --> 01:20:38.084
So, I knew this guy.

01:20:39.760 --> 01:20:41.900
Someone broke into his house
while he was sleeping.

01:20:42.000 --> 01:20:44.526
After that, he kept
a shotgun in his house.

01:20:45.960 --> 01:20:48.122
It was a 12-gauge Remington.

01:20:49.440 --> 01:20:51.340
I don't know what that means.

01:20:51.440 --> 01:20:53.620
Remington is the make.

01:20:53.720 --> 01:20:56.166
It holds seven rounds, or bullets.

01:20:56.600 --> 01:20:59.331
But in shotguns, they're called shells.

01:21:00.680 --> 01:21:01.940
Okay.

01:21:02.040 --> 01:21:05.300
So he loaded the first two shells
with bean bag rounds

01:21:05.400 --> 01:21:08.051
and the last five with regular shells.

01:21:08.560 --> 01:21:10.220
You... You lost me.

01:21:10.320 --> 01:21:13.802
Bean bag rounds
are little bags filled with lead shot.

01:21:14.440 --> 01:21:17.780
The bag is designed to protect the skin
from penetration.

01:21:17.880 --> 01:21:21.487
So, technically, they're classified
as non-lethal rounds.

01:21:22.800 --> 01:21:25.380
So, he loaded the first two shells
with bean bags

01:21:25.480 --> 01:21:29.007
because a non-lethal round
qualifies as a warning shot.

01:21:29.840 --> 01:21:30.860
Why?

01:21:30.960 --> 01:21:35.682
Firing a warning shot is self-defense,
if you're standing in front of a judge.

01:21:36.200 --> 01:21:39.488
If a perpetrator continues
to threaten your safety,

01:21:39.640 --> 01:21:43.486
any shot after that is justifiable.

01:21:47.440 --> 01:21:48.680
LEAH: So...

01:21:51.000 --> 01:21:53.810
- You're saying...
- I'm just telling you a story.

01:21:54.320 --> 01:21:56.482
What you do with that information
on your own time

01:21:57.160 --> 01:21:58.491
is none of my business.

01:22:02.440 --> 01:22:04.420
I don't like where this thing is going.

01:22:04.520 --> 01:22:07.763
We're talking because
maybe this ends badly.

01:22:09.760 --> 01:22:11.728
You don't want that. Okay?

01:22:12.680 --> 01:22:14.091
And neither do I.

01:22:18.840 --> 01:22:20.251
(INDISTINCT)

01:22:39.520 --> 01:22:41.020
Is she the next victim?

01:22:41.120 --> 01:22:42.167
WOMAN: Excuse me?

01:22:45.720 --> 01:22:46.780
What's going on here?

01:22:46.880 --> 01:22:48.564
Oh, you don't know me now?

01:22:49.880 --> 01:22:53.089
Don't believe a word
this piece of shit tells you.

01:22:53.440 --> 01:22:56.569
He fed me the same lies,
and then he stalked me.

01:22:57.560 --> 01:23:00.100
And then, he murdered
the man I was gonna marry.

01:23:00.200 --> 01:23:01.220
She's lying.

01:23:01.320 --> 01:23:03.300
Oh, and he's very charming.

01:23:03.400 --> 01:23:04.561
And persistent.

01:23:04.760 --> 01:23:08.765
Nothing will stop him, not even
restraining orders or the police.

01:23:10.720 --> 01:23:11.820
I think I should go.

01:23:11.920 --> 01:23:13.940
Good idea. Do not walk. Run.

01:23:14.040 --> 01:23:15.804
While you still can.

01:23:19.560 --> 01:23:20.925
Murderer.

01:23:32.920 --> 01:23:34.940
- (CELL PHONE BEEPS)
- KAREN: Leah, where are you?

01:23:35.040 --> 01:23:37.340
Alicia and I are worried about you.
We've left you so many messages.

01:23:37.440 --> 01:23:39.920
You gotta call us back. Please.

01:23:40.080 --> 01:23:41.286
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

01:24:54.520 --> 01:24:56.329
- TENANT: Who is it?
- Delivery.

01:24:57.840 --> 01:24:59.171
(DOOR BUZZES)

01:25:00.280 --> 01:25:03.443
- (MUFFLED HIP-HOP MUSIC)
- (MUFFLED CONVERSATIONS)

01:25:19.800 --> 01:25:21.802
(DOORKNOB RATTLING)

01:25:32.560 --> 01:25:34.562
(MUFFLED CONVERSATIONS CONTINUE)

01:26:07.560 --> 01:26:09.130
(CAT MEWLING)

01:26:10.800 --> 01:26:11.961
Rusty.

01:26:12.520 --> 01:26:13.521
Oh.

01:26:22.440 --> 01:26:23.965
(KEYBOARD CLACKING)

01:26:26.440 --> 01:26:28.488
(COMPUTER BEEPING RHYTHMICALLY)

01:26:33.760 --> 01:26:35.205
(RAPID BEEPING)

01:26:45.800 --> 01:26:47.290
(GRUNTING)

01:27:28.360 --> 01:27:30.840
MR. KESLOW: From the looks of it,
it all seems very impressive.

01:27:31.840 --> 01:27:34.571
CARTER: As I said, I look forward
to working with you in the future.

01:27:34.920 --> 01:27:37.287
- And don't worry about that...
- CINDY: Sorry to interrupt.

01:28:08.440 --> 01:28:10.124
(CROWD EXCLAIMING)

01:28:22.200 --> 01:28:24.202
(MUFFLED HIP-HOP MUSIC)

01:28:46.680 --> 01:28:48.011
(DOOR UNLOCKS)

01:29:19.680 --> 01:29:21.284
(SHOWER RUNNING)

01:30:13.000 --> 01:30:14.161
(GUN COCKS)

01:30:14.480 --> 01:30:15.606
You lost?

01:30:26.160 --> 01:30:27.321
No.

01:30:33.680 --> 01:30:37.480
Take one more step
and you're gonna feel lost.

01:30:37.640 --> 01:30:38.721
Put the gun down.

01:30:39.120 --> 01:30:40.340
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

01:30:40.440 --> 01:30:41.805
Please, Leah.

01:30:45.160 --> 01:30:46.730
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:31:00.680 --> 01:31:01.681
(GROANS)

01:31:03.560 --> 01:31:04.561
(YELPS)

01:31:47.960 --> 01:31:48.961
(STRAINING)

01:32:17.880 --> 01:32:18.881
(GROANING)

01:32:23.480 --> 01:32:25.289
- What the hell was that?
- A warning.

01:32:26.480 --> 01:32:27.845
(BOTH PANTING)

01:32:30.080 --> 01:32:31.366
(CARTRIDGE CLATTERS)

01:32:33.960 --> 01:32:35.450
You're not gonna kill me.

01:32:36.640 --> 01:32:38.860
- (GRUNTS) God!
- Maybe not.

01:32:38.960 --> 01:32:42.487
But I got five more like it,
and they will fuck you up!

01:32:45.400 --> 01:32:46.820
(LAUGHING)

01:32:46.920 --> 01:32:48.285
Something funny?

01:32:48.440 --> 01:32:49.805
(COUGHING)

01:32:53.040 --> 01:32:54.405
- (CARTRIDGE CLATTERS)
- (GROANING)

01:33:15.800 --> 01:33:17.484
(GLASS SHATTERING)

01:33:24.880 --> 01:33:26.530
(CHOKING)

01:33:28.680 --> 01:33:30.364
Looks like I lied.

01:33:57.880 --> 01:33:59.780
Ma'am, are you okay? Can I help you?

01:33:59.880 --> 01:34:02.008
I'm here to see Detective Hansen.

01:34:03.040 --> 01:34:04.371
Hansen!

01:34:12.480 --> 01:34:13.811
Come inside.

01:34:28.080 --> 01:34:30.287
I want to report an intruder.

01:34:36.760 --> 01:34:38.060
This is Hansen.

01:34:38.160 --> 01:34:42.529
I need a couple of units, Code Three,
at 12177 Lockhaven Road.

01:34:43.480 --> 01:34:44.686
Got it?

01:34:49.440 --> 01:34:50.680
Are you okay?

01:34:59.320 --> 01:35:00.606
I am now.

01:35:12.280 --> 01:35:14.681
